DESCRIPTION:COMMUNITY BENEFITS ADVISORY COUNCIL NOTICE OF PUBLIC MEETING D
 ATE: June 3 rd \, 2026 TIME: 3 p.m. LOCATION: Tampa Municipal Office Build
 ing 2 nd Floor Conference Room 306 E Jackson\, St.\, Tampa\, FL 33602 MEET
 ING PURPOSE: The purpose of this public meeting of the Community Benefits 
 Advisory Council (CBAC) is to discuss and prepare recommendations to be pr
 esented to the Mayor\, City Council\, the Developer\, and City of Tampa re
 sidents regarding proposed community benefits associated with the Sanchez 
 y Haya Project. Community benefits discussed may include\, but are not lim
 ited to\, activities in the following areas: Environmental resiliency and 
 sustainability Public infrastructure and public realm improvements Equitab
 le economic opportunities and small business support Historic preservation
  and adaptive reuse initiatives Mobility\, pedestrian\, bicycle\, and tran
 sit improvements Public art\, cultural preservation\, community gathering 
 spaces\, and neighborhood amenities Members of the public will have an opp
 ortunity to provide public comments during the meeting. VIRTUAL PARTICIPAT
