SUMMARY:CRA Community Workshop
LOCATION:Tampa \, FL United States
DESCRIPTION:TAMPA COMMUNITY REDEVELOPMENT AGENCY CRA COMMUNITY WORKSHOP NO
 TICE OF PUBLIC MEETING Date: Thursday\, June 4\, 2026 Time: 5:30  7pm Loca
 tion: Hillsborough Community College  Dale Mabry Campus Student Services B
 uilding\, Room 108 4001 W. Tampa Bay Blvd. Tampa FL 33614 Agenda: Please c
 ontact Cedric McCray at (813) 274-8325 or Cedric.McCraytampagov.net (mailt
 o:Cedric.McCraytampagov.net) Purpose: To inform the community of a propose
 d policy and grant change that has come up since the April 22 nd workshop 
 and gather community feedback to share with the CRA Board during the appro
 val process. The Tampa Community Redevelopment Agency (CRA) invites you to
  a community workshop to learn about a revised proposal for updates to CRA
  policy and the Commercial Development Grant. The proposed changes would r
 equire all Commercial Development Grant projects to include clearly identi
 fied community benefits. The update process is intended to improve transpa
 rency\, strengthen accountability for funded projects\, and better align g
 rant investments with the priorities identified in the Community Redevelop
 ment Plans (CRP) and Florida Statutes. Feedback gathered during the worksh
 op will help inform the CRA Boards consideration of the proposed updates. 
 In accordance with the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) and Section 2
 86.26\, Florida Statutes\, persons with disabilities needing a reasonable 
 accommodation to participate in this public hearing or meeting should cont
 act the City of Tampas ADA Coordinator at least 48 hours prior to the proc
 eeding. The ADA Coordinator may be contacted via phone at 813-274-3964\, e
 mail at TampaADAtampagov.net\, (mailto:TampaADAtampagov.net) or by submitt
 ing an ADA - Accommodations Request form available online at tampagov.netA
 DARequest. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/191031
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/191031
END:VEVENT
